        "INTERNAL AND EXTERNAL \n \nMANAGER: REAM \nSALARY GROUP: Management (D3) \nLOCATION: Johannesburg - Park Station Region \nDEPARTMENT: Real Estate Asset Management \nBUSINESS UNIT: PRASA CRES\nPOST NUMBER: TBA \nREFERENCE: R&S/JHB \u2013 PS /REAM/M/10/2023 \n \nDEPARTMENTAL MISSION: To manage and develop the Real Estate Portfolio of PRASA CRES to maximize the returns and follow provisions of best practice on management of regional assets.\n \nOUTPUTS:\n\u2022 Provide input and make recommendations during the development and review of REAM strategies, policies and procedures.\n\u2022 Set regional targets and monitor performance thereof.\n\u2022 Initiate and drive programs to meet shortfalls on targeted revenue projections.\n\u2022 Prepare business cases for commercialization projects.\n\u2022 Identify properties for development to enhance revenue and increase the Gross lettable Area (GLA).\n\u2022 Lead all Lease negotiations for potential clients/tenants (Commercial and Residential).\n\u2022 Identify revenue opportunities within the available rentable spaces in the portfolio.\n\u2022 Monitor all matters handed in for litigation processes.\n\u2022 Implement tenants\u2019 retention strategies for the regional portfolio.\n\n\u2022 Conduct tenant installation projects for all tenants including high profile and blue-chip clients.\n\u2022 Liaise with Corporate Security/Protection Services department in respect of the risks associated with illegal land occupation.\n\u2022 Implement controls that enable maximum recovery of municipal charges and alleviate suspension of services due to non-payment of accounts.\n\u2022 Manage, monitor, and facilitate management responses to all audit findings within the portfolio.\n\u2022 Develop controls that will ensure reduction of business risks (Revenue leaks) and ensure compliance with relevant legislation.\n\u2022 Manage human resources in terms of quality of work and application of policies (Performance Management, Leave, Time and Attendance).\n\u2022 Ensure safekeeping of REAM documents (tenant\u2019s lease files and documents).\n\u2022 Report on all REAM activities to Senior Management / Head Office. \n \nKNOWLEDGE: \n\u2022 Knowledge of Company Policies and Procedures, Internal Processes and Systems, Basic understanding of relevant legislation: PFMA, Property legislation, Contract Management legislation, OSH Act, etc., SAPOA standards,\n\u2022 Updated knowledge of general property regulations, excellent administrative skills and ability to work in a result orientated environment.\n \nSKILLS:\n\u2022 Negotiation Skills, Problem Solving Skills, Contract Management and Risk Management.\n\u2022 Report writing Skills, Relationship Management and Communication Skills - verbal and written, Financial acumen and Leadership Skills.\n\u2022 MS Office skills.\n \nATTITUDES:\n\u2022 Analytical, Integrity, Reliability, Deadline Driven, Professional, Customer focus, Quality oriented and Team Player.\n\u2022 Pro-active, Honest, Able to meet deadlines, Able to work independently, Professional, Disciplined and Result orientated.\n\u2022 Attention to Detail.\n \nCAPABILITIES:\nMinimum Requirements:\n\u2022 Grade 12 Certificate.\n\u2022 Bachelor\u2019s Degree in Real Estate or Property Management / any other Property related qualification at NQF level 7.\n\u2022 8 years\u2019 experience in Property and Asset Management and Built Environment of which a minimum of 5 years should be in a managerial position.\n\u2022 Valid code 08 Driver\u2019s license.\n \nPlease apply by submitting your CV together with the certified (not more than 3 months) copy of ID & certificates to: recruitment.sgr@prasa.com\n \nNB: APPLICATIONS i.e. CV, Certificates etc. \nTO BE SENT IN ONE PDF DOCUMENT. (PLEASE NOTE THAT INCOMPLETE APPLICATIONS WILL BE DISCARDED) \n \nCLOSING DATE: 30 November 2023 \n \nShould you not hear from us within three (3) months from the closing date, please consider your application unsuccessful. \nBy responding to this vacancy advert irrespective as to how such information is submitted, you consent to the collection, collation, processing and storing for such information and the use and disclosure of such information in accordance with the PRASA data privacy protection policy. \nPRASA shall take all reasonable measures to protect the personal information of candidates/applicants and for the purpose of this disclaimer \u201cpersonal information\u201d shall be defined as detailed in the Promotion of Access to Information Act, Act 2 of 2000 (\u201cPAIA\u201d) and the Protection of Personal Information Act, Act 4 of 2013 (\u201cPOPI\u201d) A copy of PRASA\u2019s Privacy notice is available on the website or on request. \n \nISSUED BY SENIOR MANAGER RECRUITMENT AND SELECTION \nAs per PRASA Employment Equity Plan, this position is earmarked as follows: \nMALE: African, Indian, Coloured, White\nFEMALE: African, Indian, Coloured, White "
