        " \nSOUTH AFRICAN MARITIME SAFETY AUTHORITY (SAMSA)\n ",
        " \n \nFACILITIES OFFICER\nOFFICE OF THE COO (HEAD OFFICE)\nGRADE: C4\nPERMANENT\n \nJOB PURPOSE                                                   \nTo provide support in all matters relating to the provision of facilities support services including building maintenance, on-site contractors, fleet management and housekeeping services.\n \nKEY PERFORMANCE AREAS\n\u2022 Compiling specifications for work to be carried out and assist SCM with the appointment of contractors.\n\u2022 Managing and ensuring that the air-conditioners, lifts, generator, firefighting equipment, fire detection and smoking system, electrical and plumbing requirements are attended to on a regular basis, ensuring compliance with legislation (where applicable).\n\u2022 Compiling specifications, where applicable or as and when required.\n\u2022 Participating in lease contractual agreements with Facilities Manager and Legal Section. Participating with the Facilities Manager and Sourcing/Contract Specialist/Legal Section (SCM) on contractual and other arrangements.\n\u2022 Assisting with the replacement/acquisition of copier equipment on the Transversal   Contracts.\n\u2022 Contract-ordinate all lease agreement through legal section and ensure that they are properly signed and adhere to SAMSA regulatory requirements. \n\u2022 Preparing safety records and reports on, inter alia, OHS related matters.\n\u2022 Managing the SAMSA fleet which includes the monitoring, approving of trips, overseeing that log sheets are duly completed, ensuring that drivers are in possession of valid driver\u2019s licenses, timeously renewing of vehicle licenses, managing alleged contraventions (speeding fines, etc.).\n\u2022 As Proxy SAMSA\u2019s representative for vehicles, executing all duties relating thereto.\n\u2022 Ensuring that payments are being made in accordance with contracts/invoices.\n\u2022 Assisting with the preparation of the facilities annual budget, including capital requirements\n\u2022 Ensuring that purchase orders are being issued for work to be carried out or agreements entered. \n\u2022 Participate in preparing the facilities budget and developing the facilities procurement plan.\n\u2022 Participate and provide input during the development of Facilities Management policies and procedures.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\n \nQualifications\n\u2022 National Diploma in Logistics or equivalent qualification \n \nKnowledge and Experience\n\u2022 Minimum of   5 to 7 years\u2019 related experience in Facilities Management.\n\u2022 3 years should have been at a Supervisory level.\n\u2022 Experience in Logistic management would be an advantage.\n\u2022 Basic knowledge and understanding of applicable procurement financial and other systems in use. \n \nCompetencies \n\u2022 Professionalism\n\u2022 Good communication skills\n\u2022 Time management skills\n\u2022 Computer skills\n\u2022 Attention to detail and accuracy.\n\u2022 Problem solving\n\u2022 Relationship building\n\u2022 Assertiveness\n \n \nShould you meet the requirements as set out above, please e-mail your CV to Neo Moeng at: recruitment@samsa.org.za\n \nAs we are committed to Employment Equity in our employment practices, it is our intention to appoint individuals with the aim of meeting our Equity objectives. Preference will be given to African Males, White Females and people living with a disability to achieve the objectives of Employment Equity.\n \nCLOSING DATE: 28 November 2023\n \nPlease note: SAMSA reserves the right not to make an appointment to any advertised position. No late applications will be considered. Psychometric and other assessments may be used as part of the selection process and all shortlisted candidates will be required to be available for the tests. If you have not been contacted within 1 month of the closing date as mentioned above, kindly deem your application unsuccessful.\n \n \n \n \n ",
        "PRINCIPAL OFFICER: PORT OF MOSSELBAY\nGRADE: D4\nPERMANENT\nSOUTHERN REGION\n \nJOB PURPOSE\nTo perform the duties of a Principal Officer and to manage a SAMSA Port Office in accordance with the requirements of the Merchant Shipping Act, all other Acts and regulations that are administered by SAMSA as well as the principles and objectives of the business plan and to be accountable for the cost-effective day-to-day management of the office.\n \nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES\n\u2022   Ensure safe ships and clean seas: Conduct surveys, inspections and investigations. Render advice in accordance with statutory laws & regulations. Deliver an effective Survey Strategy and \n    Flag State Implementation. Implement Port State Control. Ensure that policy is exercised effectively. Ensure that data is being captured.\n\u2022  Uphold and implement legislation: Co-ordinate and integrate the initiation, participation and contribution towards the drafting of proposed legislation, regulations, and amendments to\n\n    legislation, regulations, and policy. Fulfil national and international maritime safety and anti-pollution responsibilities and obligations.\n\u2022  Financial Management: Ensure provision and generation of adequate funds and capital requirements for the office, as well as the prudent utilization of funds and control of expenditure.\n\u2022  Management of staff: Manage the performance of staff to ensure competence and the realization of the regional operational plan.\n\u2022  People Management: Supervise daily activities, and manage the performance, training, and development of staff to ensure competence. Set goals, Empower, Coach, and Mentor staff, and\n   create a workplace culture that is consistent with the values of SAMSA.\n\u2022  Stakeholder Management: Build and sustain relationships with internal and external stakeholders and manage stakeholder expectations. Promote customer care as a key objective.\n \nREQUIREMENTS\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\u2022 A STCW Master unlimited or STCW Chief Engineering unlimited is required.\n\u2022 Any additional qualification in the Maritime field will be advantageous\n\u2022 Driver\u2019s licence is required.\n \nEXPERIENCE\n\u2022 A minimum of 3 years\u2019 experience doing ship surveying at SAMSA.\n\u2022 Previous managerial experience, preferably in a related field, is advantageous\n \nCOMPETENCIES\n\u2022 Strategic thinking\n\u2022 Decision making\n\u2022 Problem-solving\n\u2022 Leading\n \n \nShould you meet the requirements as set out above, please e-mail your CV and recently certified copies of your qualifications to: Babalwa Venge at Recruitment4@samsa.org.za\n \nAs we are committed to Employment Equity in our employment practices, it is our intention to appoint individuals with the aim of meeting our equity objectives. Preference will be given to African Male and members of the designated groups to achieve the objectives of Employment Equity. Candidates with disability are encouraged to apply.\n \nClosing date: 28 NOVEMBER 2023\n \nPlease note: SAMSA reserves the right not to make an appointment to any advertised position. No late applications will be considered. Psychometric and other assessments may be used as part of the selection process and all shortlisted candidates will be required to be available for the tests. If you have not been contacted within 1 month of the closing date as mentioned above, kindly deem your application unsuccessful.",
        "X1 ENGINE SURVEYOR\nPERMANENT \nGRADE: (D3) \nOFFICE: PORT ELIZABETH\n \nThe above position will report to the Principal Officer\n \nJOB PURPOSE\nTo ensure vessels, seafarers and maritime service providers are compliant with applicable maritime legislation and relevant maritime Conventions; to give effect to the objectives of the South African Maritime Safety Authority (SAMSA) and the International Maritime Organization (IMO) Instruments.\n \nKEY PERFORMANCE AREAS \n\u2022 Ship Surveys and Inspections: Undertake all Statutory Surveys, Audits and Inspections in accordance with applicable legislation and other relevant regulations relating to Marine Pollution Prevention and Safety. Give effect to our obligation under the Instruments relevant to the III Code (Tonnage, COLREGS, Load line, SOLAS, MARPOL)\n\u2022 Examinations and Accreditations: Give full and complete effect to the International Convention on Standards of Training, Certification and Watchkeeping for Seafarers (STCW), 1978 in accordance with the provisions of section A-I/8 of the STCW Code, whereby all training, assessment of competence, certification, including medical certification, endorsement and revalidation activities are carried out, by applying appropriate domestic legislation. Comply with the Quality Standards System of SAMSA to ensure alignment with STCW. \n\u2022 Legislation Regulations and Policy: Review, recommend and contribute towards drafting maritime regulations and amendments. Review and Draft Marine Notices and Marine Circulars. Review, recommend and Draft SAMSA Policies and Procedures. Participate in ad hoc projects as and when required in line with level of responsibilities.\n\u2022 Casualty/Incident Investigations: Undertake casualty / incident investigations Produce reports and make recommendations timeously. Fulfil an expert witness role in a Marine Court of Enquiry.\n\u2022 Stakeholder Management: Provide consultancy services to Industry Stakeholders. Participate in and report on local, regional and international fora and make recommendations. Manage and engage with Stakeholders in accordance with SAMSA Core Values.\n \n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\n\u2022 Chief or Second Engineer Officer (no limitation) COC \n\u2022 STCW ancillary courses and any other equivalent training\n\u2022 Sailed in rank of Second Engineer (seagoing experience) is preferable.\n \nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS, TRAINING AND EXPERIENCE\n \n\u2022 STCW Compliant COC - Chief or Second Engineer (STCW III/2 \u2013 no limitation) \n\u2022 STCW ancillary courses \n\u2022 Sailed in rank of Chief Engineer or Second Engineer Officer\n\u2022 Maritime experience for a period of 2-3 years in a management role is preferable\n\u2022 Driver\u2019s License\n\u2022 Own Transport\n\u2022 Preferred Medical Clearance Certificate \u2013 obtained from a SAMSA approved medical practitioner\n\u2022 Ability to travel as and when required.\n\u2022 Valid Passport\n \n \nShould you meet the requirements set out above, please e-mail your CV to Babalwa Venge Recruitment4@samsa.org.za\n \nClosing date: 28 November 2023\n \nAs we are committed to Employment Equity in our employment practices, it is our intention to appoint individuals with the aim of meeting our Equity objectives. Preference will given to African Male and candidates that meets the EE targets in line with the organisational EE plan.\n \nPlease note: SAMSA reserves the right not to make an appointment to any advertised position. No late applications will be considered. Psychometric and other assessments may be used as part of the selection process and all shortlisted candidates will be required to be available for the tests. If you have not been contacted within 1 month of the closing date as mentioned above, kindly deem your application unsuccessful."
