        " \nGAUTENG DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH\n \nSTUDY MEDICINE IN CUBA 2024\n \nNELSON MANDELA FIDEL CASTRO PROGRAMME\n \nGauteng Department of Health invites all Prospective students from disadvantaged communities who are interested in studying Medicine in Cuba for 2024 intake.\n ",
        " \nREQUIREMENTS:\n\u2022 Candidates must have a university entrance Grade12 with minimum level 4 of pass marks in the following subjects: Physical Science, Maths, Biology/Life Sciences and English.\n\u2022 Applicants must be South African citizens and permanently residing in Gauteng must have matriculated in Gauteng.\n\u2022 Must be between the age of 18-30 years.\nApplication forms are available online and from Gauteng Department of Health facilities and District Health Services Offices.\n \n \nNB: The application forms should be accompanied by the Curriculum Vitae (CV) with the following documents:\n \nTwo (2) certified copies of:\n\u2022 Birth Certificate\n\u2022 Identification document - (applicant and parents/guardians ID)\n\u2022 National Senior Certificate (Matric)\n\u2022 Proof of income (Payslips) of both parents or guardians - (sworn affidavits for those without proof of income/ unemployed)\n\u2022 Proof of residence validated by the Ward Councillor and Municipality Bill.",
        "ALL COMPLETED APPLICATIONS MUST BE HAND DELIVERED TO THE FOLLOWING ADDRESS:\n\nGauteng Department of Health | 2nd Floor Room 209| 45 Commissioner Street, Life Centre Building Marshalltown, Johannesburg, 2107\n \nEnquiries: Ms. Rebecca Moema 082 848 1594 | Ms Julia Zwane 083 496 9252 | Ms Mapula Motaung 082 737 7130\n \nOnly successful applicants will be contacted. If you have not heard from the Department within three (3) months after the closing date, please accept that your application was unsuccessful.\n \nCLOSING DATE - 30 NOVEMBER 2023"
